Feature Backlog:

- Develop Story / Game Rules
- Creative tutorial

- Character and Inventory 
      - implement Character persistance 
- High-Scores / leaderboard
      - implement leaderboard persistance
- Illustrate / develop / Integrate GUI
- Design and implement individual rooms
      - Unique instances in each room to roll vs skill to find,avoid,escape,succeed 
- Random Dice generator class for skill checks
- Create Item list / weight system
- Experience system / point allocation
- Processing of variable user input

- Consider and Design JUnit tests
- Create JDocs / Instruction documentation

As a player, I want to be able to challenge other players.

As a player, I want to be able to choose which room I want to start playing in.

As a player, I want to be able to see other player's score.

As a player, I want to be able to quit the game when I want.

As a player, I want to be able to save my game stats.

As a player, I want to be able to roll against my skills to steal an item.

As a player, I want the system for getting caught to be implemented.

As a player, I want the leaderboard system to be created so I can check it and have my scores posted on it.

As a player, I want the there to be five rooms to explore with plenty of items to get.

As a player, I want to be able to level my skills.

As a player, I want to be able to see the help menu.






